cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.MM. 

This paper deals with image retrieval tasks and proposes a method to enhance the invariance of off-the-shelf convolutional neural network features. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also uses reinforcement learning to learn an ensemble of beneficial image transformations, which suggests a possible fit with cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves learning and optimization, which could be relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also evaluates its proposed method using experiments, which could be relevant to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
